> I have heard that there is a way I can talk to you to input prompts
  ⎿  ⧉ Selected 61 lines from memory-bank/memory-bank-activeContext.md in Visual Studio Code

⏺ Yes! There are voice input options depending on your setup:

  1. macOS/iOS Built-in Dictation

  - Enable: System Settings → Keyboard → Dictation (turn on)
  - Use: Press Fn twice (or configured hotkey) to start dictation
  - Works in: Any text field, including Claude Code terminal prompts
  - Pros: Built-in, no extra tools, works offline
  - Cons: May have pauses, punctuation requires speaking ("comma", "period")

  2. Browser Voice Input (if using Claude web)

  - Chrome/Edge: Right-click in text field → "Voice typing"
  - Pros: Good accuracy, free
  - Cons: Only works in browser

  3. Third-Party Tools

  - Whisper (OpenAI): Very accurate transcription app
  - Dragon: Professional dictation software
  - Talon Voice: Hands-free coding (advanced, but powerful)

  4. Claude Code Terminal (if you're using terminal)

  - Use macOS dictation or pipe from a voice tool
  - Example workflow: Speak → Dictation → Terminal input

  ---
  For your workflow:
  Since you're using Claude Code (likely via terminal), macOS Dictation is easiest:
  1. Enable in System Settings
  2. Press Fn Fn in terminal
  3. Speak your prompt
  4. Press Fn again to stop

  Want help setting it up?

> yes

⏺ Great! Let's set up macOS Dictation for Claude Code.

  Step-by-Step Setup:

  1. Enable Dictation on macOS

  1. Click  → System Settings
  2. Go to Keyboard
  3. Scroll down to Dictation section
  4. Toggle Dictation to ON
  5. Choose language: English (United States) or your preferred dialect
  6. Set shortcut: Default is Press Fn (Globe) Key Twice
    - You can change this to another key combo if preferred

  2. Test It

  1. Open any text field (Notes app, TextEdit, etc.)
  2. Press Fn twice quickly
  3. You'll see a microphone icon appear
  4. Speak: "Hello, this is a test."
  5. Press Fn once to stop
  6. Text should appear

  3. Use with Claude Code

  1. Open your terminal where Claude Code runs
  2. At the Claude Code prompt, press Fn twice
  3. Speak your prompt (examples below)
  4. Press Fn once to stop
  5. Press Enter to send

  Tips for Better Accuracy:

  Punctuation commands:
  - Say "comma" → ,
  - Say "period" → .
  - Say "question mark" → ?
  - Say "new line" → ↵
  - Say "cap" before a word to capitalize it

  Example spoken prompts:
  - "In the schedule a workout dialogue comma add a button to clear all filters period"
  - "Fix the hover preview so it appears above the card instead of on top of it period"
  - "Search for all uses of movement extraction and explain how it works period"

  Pro tip: Speak naturally, but pause slightly for punctuation words.

  ---
  Try it now:
  1. Enable Dictation in System Settings
  2. Come back here and try dictating your next request to me

  Let me know if you hit any issues!

